    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Corwin</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Seward</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                    States</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">City of
                                        Mexico</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I deem it of the very first importance that our consuls at every port on
                            the Gulf of Mexico should be at their respective posts, with careful and
                            specific instructions as to their treatment of vessels sailing under the
                            flag of the Confederate States, or having papers from ports within those
                            States, made out by officers under their authority.</p>
                <pb facs="0070" n="70" xml:id="pg_70"/>
                <p>Should the relations now existing, or which may hereafter exist, between
                            the United States and the seceding States be such as to require of me
                            any specific act in relation to such state of things, I beg to be
                            advised of it by the department as early as possible.</p>
                <p>The present government of Mexico is well affected towards us in our
                            present difficulties, but, for obvious reasons, will be unwilling to
                            enter into any engagement which might produce war with the south, unless
                            protected by promise of aid from the United States.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>THOMAS CORWIN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">W. H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
